## RULES
- ✅ Java standard library imports first
- ✅ Framework imports (Spring, Jmix) grouped together
- ✅ Project imports last (before static imports)
- ✅ Static imports always last
- ✅ Blank line between import groups
- ✅ No blank lines within same group
- ✅ Alphabetical order within each group

## PALANTIR BASELINE ENFORCEMENT
Import order is automatically enforced by Palantir Baseline via Spotless.
- Run `./gradlew format` to auto-format all Java files (includes imports, unused imports removal, whitespace)
- Run `./gradlew spotlessApply` for Spotless-only formatting
- Palantir Baseline automatically configures: `importOrder`, `removeUnusedImports`, `trimTrailingWhitespace`, `endWithNewline`

**Note**: Palantir Baseline's default import order groups all `com.*` imports together (including `com.digtp.*`).
This is the standard Baseline behavior and is acceptable for this project.
According to Palantir Java Style Guide, project imports (`com.digtp.*`) should ideally come after third-party `com.*` imports,
but Baseline's automatic grouping is a practical compromise that works well in practice.

